 First and formost, I belive that it is important to adapt your point of view to fit the situation, like when you read my former post ,I assume you tried to see my point, yet you grasp it only partially(i assume the extent of your perception from what you said in your reply)and that you miss a major portion: that the quest for fact is limited by our perception of the world,and all things pretaining to our/your/my perception on reality and how we daily define ourselves through our actions only partially and our thoughts completely.<br>
 To simplify,we rely upon faith(in something,or anything)to cover the wall were our understandig ends.Take Religion,(though i may be opening the famous &quot;can of worms&quot;in saying this)many people put faith in something they cannot tangibly sense,but rely upon it all the same.Not to say that there is nothing to be said for the applications of the reality we create to the spiritual relm or lack thereof,but to say that faith creates a truth and that the truth is adaptabe to each person who speaks what they think,or thier own personal definition of the truth.To say that the adaptability of the truth has no limits and that one could do whatever one wants as long as thier personal morals don't conflict would be insane,from the general point of view of society.Law is there to maintain order,and the law defines the truth so that a person will have to obey the wishes of the general populus.<br>
The purpose of law in general relation to the desires or wishes of the general populus is best defined by the &quot;3,000 tyrants one mile away&quot; statement in &quot;The Patriot&quot;.One mans rights can be toppled just as easily by a free nation with some limits as in a limited nation with some freedom.Just as a man designs his own truths,belifs,and reality, society designs the limitations to constrict them with what truths,beliefs and reality is acceptable.No,i am not saying that society is wrong ,i am saying that because we define our reality,we must rely upon the borders of society to prevent the chaos that would result if no man had borders and each individual differed in opinion dramatically from the next.Society's borders keep or realities in some semblance of order,and thus must be upheld.<br>
 Now,back to my first statement,that Fact is a Fantasy.Facts rely upon a general agreement that something is the truth,and we cannot obtain this in our current society.<br>
I await the reply of a differing or similar viewpoint and will return Monday to see this view.<br>
           <br>
                                  -Kaden<br>
